<h3><i>Striking Distance</i> _ Anna Remus</h3> 
<p>2024, English subtitles</p>
<p>Echoes of home, the sun warming your skin, and the realization that you never belonged.
</p>

<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/08c167160eb4a3eed9763dfad28b1176/f617df6d73fb1ab1-51/s2048x3072/d7c9c6e85098ecb0d3886185921572c595c0d730.jpg" alt="turning point" class="responsive">


<h3><i> 까치 눈 / Magpie Eye</i> _ Jonathan Seungjoon Lee</h3> 
<p>2025, Korean/English</p>
<p>Magpie Eye is an analog film work that explores the immaterial realities of our world through the lens of Korean dream journey traditions (monguyrok). Using a 16mm handmade pinhole camera, the work captures ritual sites, sacred trees, and activist sites in Jeju Island. Like the magpie's iridescent blue that appears beneath its seemingly black and white feathers, the film reveals what is invisible or dismissed as unreal, offering an alternative way of seeing and understanding the spirit world around us. 
</p>

<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/2a7a236843f1656a2d849b305170ebef/f617df6d73fb1ab1-74/s2048x3072/83539ce3966c9c468e2a4a976207d2fb4edcafee.pnj" alt="magpie eye" class="responsive">


<h3><i>Triptych</i> _ Ulla Reiss</h3>
<p>2026, English / Russian (Film 3) w/ English subs, 8mm</p>
<p>A series of three short experimental films exploring shifting states of self.
Presence. Fragmentation. Motion.
</p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/185e61ca8eb05725d23d7b4f18ad147d/f617df6d73fb1ab1-09/s2048x3072/ccde75fb325c7b4a6a85b848dbd953c42d7cd9db.pnj" alt="triptych" class="responsive"> 

<h3><i>Softer Skin</i> _ Will Haydon</h3>
<p>2025</p>
<p>A macro film charting an enigmatic transformation that sweeps through a human landscape, and a meditation on the desire to change without knowing what you will become. </p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/46eccd0f0a1f632ea6795d49d421148c/f617df6d73fb1ab1-c5/s640x960/a1f5730879c65efe0e3692bc084b4afaefd30858.pnj" alt="softer skin" class="responsive">


<h3><i>Blue Transcendence</i> _ Erica Schreiner</h3>
<p>2022</p>
<p>Filmed on VHS in Erica's apartment, Blue Transcendence takes us on a psychedelic journey with blue butterflies, a performance in blue, and a time-lapse of a candle burning during a magical spell. The film reflects on real friendship and the importance of being silly.
</p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/6410ceb73e7cf4ab281ff963844859c6/f617df6d73fb1ab1-3e/s2048x3072/c8a7fbedbe561e745d6ceebe2afbe3af0df40fd8.pnj" alt="Blue Transcendence" class="responsive"> 


<h3><i>Noise to Signal</i> _ Guan Huang</h3>
<p>2024</p>
<p>Filmed in a single zoom-out shot by a DV camera. As the tone of the background noise gradually falls, the filmed object transitions from the flicking pixies on a display screen to the actual spatial context of the screen. 
</p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/c3f5dfbfa5cde7624c70c75fd90046d2/f617df6d73fb1ab1-28/s1280x1920/e74d6f603936e652b78c41ee5a04bd098f0a341b.pnj" alt="" class="responsive"> 

<h3><i>Poor Mr. Nixon</i> _ Julia Cooke</h3>
<p>2023</p>
<p>The true story of Richard Nixon.
</p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/1f15ef1e78bb33928b3d7deb761429be/f617df6d73fb1ab1-48/s1280x1920/9c835029df6822fc593ea1540f7a4b196533e724.pnj" alt="Nixon" class="responsive"> 

<h3><i>Absolute Divinity</i> _ Joslyn Crocco</h3>
<p>2025</p>
<p>Absolute Divinity is an audio / visual project that connects themes of nature & technology through the synthesis of generative visuals & the human spirit.
</p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/47e1adea4247798f0e78b7f04f4607ac/f617df6d73fb1ab1-04/s2048x3072/8f909514b55d3f28160b557f6427e5723ea255d5.pnj" alt="divinity" class="responsive"> 

<h3><i>On Ye Monkey’s Branch (or pink sands unlimited)</i> _ Walter Smits</h3>
<p>2026</p>
<p>After crash landing on a fantasy jungle island, two puppets discuss sexuality and intimacy.
</p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/8df5bdd0869a6ff6aca85152c41ebb7c/a4dd588e1dd93c30-2b/s1280x1920/c8ef7b252d446462368e22cd77ab1264cacca628.jpg" alt="monkey" class="responsive"> 

<h3><i>Green Moon</i> _ Rebecca Shenfeld</h3>
<p>2026</p>
<p>Green Moon is an experimental animation that moves through different corners of the brain at work: impulse, control, fantasy, repetition. It uses gaussian splatting to capture the main character in different outfits made and designed from scratch by Rebecca.
</p>
<img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/2da7fef16d0264f96b1d0bc78fa282d0/f617df6d73fb1ab1-f2/s2048x3072/0a771e4e502a6e9af0b0014c984dc92c6da58bcd.pnj" alt="green moon" class="responsive"> 

